<Author>brooklyn238
<Content>Nice affordable choice on the beach, although with its problems. We are pretty low-key couple who didn't need a lot of frills, just a weekend getaway on the beach, so the Beach House Hotel was a good fit -- affordably priced, located near the airport (we had late arriving and early departing flights), and right on the beach. I must say, the location on the beach is really this hotel's best feature. The beds and cabanas outside on the beach are great, as well as beach-side service for drinks/food etc. Hanging out on the cabanas at night is definitely a lot of fun as well. The complimentary breakfast is extremely basic....mini-boxes of cereal, some sad pieces of fruit, and coffe/tea. Not great, but did the job. The restaurant on the beach is decent, and service was fine.The rooms definitely could use a lot of improvement. We spotted a few cockroaches and only had hot water once during our weekend stay. Apparently there were problems/construction at the hotel (or maybe the city too?) The decor makes it seem hip and trendy, but is really just covering up some levels of crustiness. Location was great. We were able to walk to other fancy hotels eat at their restaurants, go to the casinos, etc. Would probably not stay here next time, but would definitely stay at a neighboring hotel and enjoy the day relaxing on their chairs/lounges and eating at the bar. If you are considering this hotel, I think it'd suffice for a really short trip (no more than 3 nights.) Although the beach-side amenities are great, you can still access them even if you aren't staying at the hotel. 
