<Author>billoga
<Content>Would never go back... I stayed at the Beach House for a long weekend and although the place is very chic, modern and romantic the service was just awful. It's a shame that such a nice place has such unattentive, unhelpful, rude and unhospitable staff. This is the Caribbean people!! Could you try smiling? We checked in and not one word was said to us about the place. The rooms were very small and looked nothing like the pictures on the internet. I hate to complain but truth is, the floors were dirty, the bathroom was dirty, looked like someone walked on the bed to fix light bulb and didn't wipe their shoes. It's really annoying when people don't pay any attention to details or inform their patrons of what's going on. There was a private party every night so the locals take over the whole place (it's tiny, only about 15 rooms) and don't exactly make you feel welcomed. So we tried the local hangouts but don't bother asking about the nightlife in town because no one knows a thing! Staff was not informative at all...ok, there are always one or two that will help but management was horrible. It was like they were living in a box in their own perfect worlds and were actually annoyed that they had guests. Asked which bus to take to Old San Juan (gorgeous btw) and everyone looked around like they didn't know what to do. Unbelievable! I would never go back and would not recommend it. I gave it 2 stars because a couple of staff members (host, cleaning lady) were nice. Very pretentious and cold...and you can get that in Miami! Another sad thing about PR in general, there is no culture. Couldn't find a Salsa/Merengue club anywhere (don't ask hotel staff either because they don't know). Also, this place is pricey...NYC prices for drinks. Skip it and go across the street to Pino's and you'll get cheap drinks with generous amounts of booze and down home PR cooking! I'll toast to that!! 
