<Author>brazell
<Content>The Perfect Spot Unique and boutique are overused these days in the hotel realm, but at The Beach House, we got exactly what we were looking for. The tiny hotel right on Isla Verde combines a laid back attitude with fresh style to really mirror the spirit of San Juan. We arrived very late on a Thursday night. After a quick trip to our rooms, we dashed to La Plage, the hotel鈥檚 beachfront bar and restaurant and had the best mojitos on the planet. The DJ was spinning and a local crowd of fun beauties were enjoying a perfect evening. We knew we picked the right spot.With drinks in hand, the manager invited us to tour our temporary home. We were shown the large indoor lounge venue, La Folie, along with the breakfast area. Along the way, we were provided with a run down of the activities planned in the upcoming days. These included DJ parties, beach service and Sunday brunch. This made planning rather simple. Our room was clean and spare, exactly what it should be for a beach front hotel. There were lots of little touches, however, that made the room bright and hip, including colorful textiles, interesting pottery and gorgeous flowers. The spa amenities were nice, and we made use of the ipod docking station too. We ate at La Plage three times. These were the absolute best meals that we had during our stay in Puerto Rico. The Paella is better than 75% of the paella that I have had in Spain and other tapas style appetizers were original and delicious. Just like the rest of the hotel, the service was similar to what you would find as a guest in the home of your most gracious friend. We will absolutely be back. This is a place to go, if you wish to instantly plug into a very nice scene, complete with excellent hosts, a perfect spot on the beach, and a seemingly effortless ambience of cool. 
