<Author>thomasbythewater
<Content>A new find! I travel to San Juan often for business and I have stayed at the Normandie for a couple of years now. I like the Normandie, but it seems to have lost its vibe and it seems to be falling apart. I know W hotel is going to be taking over but it still seems like its wavering at the moment. I heard about a new hotel in the Isla Verde area called The Beach House, I thought I would give it a shot. The Beach Houes Hotel is a boutique hotel located right on the beach, this was really nice for my morning run on the beach etc. The hotel has a nice vibe and it seems to be getting a lot of cool tourist from the New York City area. I was surprised to see a great mix of sexy locals and NYC people hanging out on the beach and having fun. The restaurant is very packed at night and they have large video projections of different concerts and shows above the dining room. Many people opted to have drinks on the beach beds, they have real lounge type beds in the sand on the beach and are surrounded by tiki torches at night, great place for a romantic date, I will bring my girlfriend next time. The rooms are very simple and clean...i like the ipod docking station. The rooms are very relaxing and if you are looking for more action, just step outside. I will be returning for work monthly in San Juan and I think I have found a new cool place for me to stay while in Puerto Rico. 
